{"key":"post-11135981","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11135981</id>\n<content>I don't use a rack between jars.&amp;nbsp; I stagger them and stack them up, sometimes five or six high.&amp;nbsp; When you move to substrate bags, you should put spacers between them to allow the steam to penetrate all the way around each bag.&amp;nbsp; This is because the bags are much larger than jars and they tend to stick together, making it hard for the heat to penetrate to the middle of the substrate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11225894</next>\n<prev>11134754</prev>\n<first>11134650</first>\n<last>11226008</last>\n<when>1254059187</when>\n<utime>09/27/09 04:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}